- The access_logs table has columns: id (UUID), user_id (UUID nullable), action (TEXT), ip_address (TEXT nullable), success (BOOLEAN), details (TEXT nullable), created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
- The users table has: id (UUID), username (TEXT UNIQUE), email (TEXT UNIQUE), password_hash (TEXT), display_name (TEXT nullable), account_state (TEXT DEFAULT 'active'), created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ), updated_at (TIMESTAMPTZ)
- The roles table has: id (SERIAL), name (TEXT UNIQUE), description (TEXT nullable)
- The user_roles table has: user_id (UUID), role_id (INT)

